   11/07/2011 - Mis à jour : 01/08/2011 - A network of partners - Tout
   thème
   A network of partners

A network of partners

   The DSS overseas the different funds and bodies that finance France’s
   social security system : CADES (social debt sinking fund), CNSA
   (national solidarity fund for continuing care), Fonds CMU (universal
   health coverage fund), FRR (pensions reserve fund), FIVA (asbestos
   victims’ compensation fund) and FSV (old-age solidarity fund).
   It services the Social Security Accounts Commission (Commission
   des comptes de la Sécurité sociale), the Inter-schemes Compensation
   Commission (Commission de compensation inter-régimes) and the Economic
   Committee for Health Care Products (Comité économique des
   produits de santé).

   It is an active participant in the work of the following bodies :
   Higher
   Council for the Future of Health Insurance (Haut conseil pour l’avenir
   de l’assurance maladie), Pensions Advisory Council (Conseil
   d’orientation
   pour les retraites), Employment Advisory Council (Conseil d’orientation
   pour l’emploi), Council of Compulsory Levies, (Conseil des
   prélèvements obligatoires), Public Finances Advisory Council (Conseil
   d’orientation des finances publiques) and the policy forum on quality
   in
   the accounts of the French social security institutions.


